verbs.description: unexpress (third-person singular simple present unexpresses, present participle unexpressing, simple past and past participle unexpressed)

entries.meaning: (transitive, rare) Hypothetically, to undo the expressing of.
examples: For Barthes, the task of the novelist is to unexpress what has already been expressed, to deliberately play havoc with what is undeniably — and therefore frustratingly — true.
